articles.description: Members of the Michigan State faculty voted 61-4 to express no confidence in the eight-member governing body at the university. Meanwhile, the institution's interim president wrote to the campus community about cooperation with ongoing investigations.
articles.headline: Michigan State faculty delivers no-confidence vote on board of trustees

images.caption: The Michigan State faculty's vote against the board of trustees came largely in response to the board's decision to name John Engler the school's interim president.
images.name: John Engler [600x400] - Copy (2)

images.caption: Michigan State students, including one who jumped onto and sat on the middle of a table, interrupt an MSU board of trustees meeting to protest the school's selection of John Engler as the interim president.
images.name: MSU students vent frustration over interim president selection

videos.description: Michigan State's Nick Ward gets the ball down low and finishes the tricky layup to start the game.
videos.headline: Ward finishes tough layup to open game

videos.description: Michigan State's Lourawls Nairn Jr. lobs a pass at the rim for Miles Bridges for the loud dunk in the first half.
videos.headline: Bridges throws down alley-oop

videos.description: Michigan State's Nick Ward finds Josh Langford cutting to the rim and feeds him for the emphatic dunk.
videos.headline: Ward finds Langford for the slam

videos.description: Michigan State's Lourawls Nairn Jr. leads Josh Langford up the court for a layup and a foul, setting up a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: MSU's Langford makes tough layup for and-one chance

videos.description: Michigan State's Miles Bridges grabs the offensive rebound and throws down the one-handed dunk in the first half.
videos.headline: Bridges throws down emphatic slam

videos.description: Akwasi Yeboah tries driving to the lane but Gavin Schilling swats the shot attempt away.
videos.headline: Spartans' Schilling denies Yeboah

videos.description: Freshman Xavier Tillman denies two shot attempts in the first half.
videos.headline: MSU's Tillman rejects back-to-back shots

videos.description: Michigan States Miles Bridges left the court after appearing to roll his ankle while driving to the basket against Stony Brook.
videos.headline: MSU's Bridges limps off with apparent ankle injury

videos.description: Nick Ward grabs the offensive rebound and goes up strong with the layup for a chance at a 3-point play.
videos.headline: Ward extends Spartans' lead on and-1
